{"id":26218,"date":"2018-04-17T13:04:37","date_gmt":"2018-04-17T09:04:37","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=26218"},"modified":"2025-03-08T11:20:59","modified_gmt":"2025-03-08T07:20:59","slug":"how-you-prefer-yourselves-servants","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/04\/17\/how-you-prefer-yourselves-servants\/","title":{"rendered":"Umar on Servants: How can you prefer yourselves over your servants?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn Abbas reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, passed by some people one day who were eating while their servants were standing. Umar said, \u201cWhy do I not see your servants eating with you? Do you not desire them?\u201d A man said, \u201cNo, by Allah, O leader of the faithful. Rather, we have preference over them.\u201d Umar became very angry, then he said, \u201cWhat is the matter with people who prefer themselves over their servants? Allah Almighty will deal with them and it is done!\u201d Then Umar said to the servants, \u201cSit down and eat.\u201d The servants sat to eat and the leader of the faithful did not eat.<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad al-Fa\u0304ru\u0304q 2\/247<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0628\u0627\u0633 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0645\u0631 \u0639\u0645\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u0637\u0627\u0628 \u0631\u0636\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647 \u064a\u0648\u0645\u0627\u064b \u0641\u0631\u0623\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0648\u0645 \u064a\u0623\u0643\u0644\u0648\u0646 \u0648\u0642\u0627\u0645 \u0627\u0644\u062e\u064f\u062f\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0645 \u0641\u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0639\u0645\u0631\u064f \u0645\u0627\u0644\u064a \u0644\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0631\u0649 \u062e\u064f\u062f\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064e\u0643\u0645 \u064a\u0623\u0643\u0644\u0648\u0646 \u0645\u0639\u0643\u0645 \u0623\u062a\u0631\u063a\u0628\u0648\u0646 \u0639\u0646\u0647\u0